"title": "5277: criminals",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5277",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Individuals who are guilty of crimes such as murder, adultery, theft, perjury or treason. Scripture refers to and gives examples of young law-breakers (delinquents).</p>\n<h2>Criminals guilty of murder</h2>\n<h3>Cain</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:8\">GEN 4:8</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Abimelech</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:5\">JDG 9:5</a></p>\n<h3>Doeg the Edomite</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam22:18\">1SA 22:18</a></p>\n<h3>David</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:14-2Sam11:17\">2SA 11:14–11:17</a></p>\n<h3>Absalom</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam13:23-2Sam13:29\">2SA 13:23–13:29</a></p>\n<h3>Herod the Great</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:16\">MAT 2:16</a></p>\n<h3>Barabbas</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:7\">MRK 15:7</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:19\">LUK 23:19</a></p>\n<h2>Criminals guilty of adultery</h2>\n<h3>David</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:2-2Sam11:5\">2SA 11:2–11:5</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Gomer (Hosea's wife)</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos3:1\">HOS 3:1</a></p>\n<h2>Criminals guilty of theft</h2>\n<h3>Rachel</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:19\">GEN 31:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:30\">GEN 31:30</a></p>\n<h3>Achan</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:21\">JOS 7:21</a></p>\n<h3>Judas Iscariot</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:6\">JHN 12:6</a></p>\n<h2>Criminals guilty of perjury</h2>\n<h3>Joel and Abijah (sons of Samuel)</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:3\">1SA 8:3</a></p>\n<h3>Two who gave false evidence against Naboth</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:13\">1KI 21:13</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of criminals guilty of treason</h2>\n<h3>Zimri</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs16:15-1Kgs16:18\">1KI 16:15–16:18</a></p>\n<h3>Athaliah</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs11:1-2Kgs11:3\">2KI 11:1–11:3</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr22:10-2Chr22:12\">2CH 22:10–22:12</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of delinquents</h2>\n<h3>Those who break the fifth commandment as minors may have been treated as criminals</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:12\">EXO 20:12</a></p>\n<h3>Manasseh, king of Judah</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs21:1-2Kgs21:2\">2KI 21:1–21:2</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Youths who jeered Elisha</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs2:23-2Kgs2:24\">2KI 2:23–2:24</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Those who ignore the wise counsel of Solomon</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:1-Prov1:4\">PRO 1:1–1:4</a></strong> <em>It seems that sections of Proverbs were written with young people in mind. Those who choose to act upon its wisdom will please God and keep themselves out of the troubles common to youth.</em></p>\n<h3>Those who succumb to the evil desires of youth</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:22\">2TI 2:22</a> <em>Young people are warned that the strength of their desires can easily get them into trouble. Young Christians are, with God's help, able to control such desires.</em></p>\n<h2>The punishment of criminals</h2>\n<h3>By hanging</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:22-Deut21:23\">DEU 21:22–21:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam21:9\">2SA 21:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra6:11\">EZR 6:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth7:9-Esth7:10\">EST 7:9–7:10</a></p>\n<h3>By stoning</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:23-Deut22:24\">DEU 22:23–22:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:1-Lev20:2\">LEV 20:1–20:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:24-Josh7:25\">JOS 7:24–7:25</a></p>\n<h3>By beating</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:2-Deut25:3\">DEU 25:2–25:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:20-Acts16:23\">ACT 16:20–16:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:24-2Cor11:25\">2CO 11:24–11:25</a></p>\n<h3>By confiscation of property</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra7:26\">EZR 7:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:8\">EZR 10:8</a></p>\n<h3>By crucifixion</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:32-Luke23:33\">LUK 23:32–23:33</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:38\">MAT 27:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:27\">MRK 15:27</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:40-Luke23:41\">LUK 23:40–23:41</a></p>",
